      "instruction": "Preheat oven to 375\u00b0. In a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. Season chicken generously with salt and pepper and sear, skin-side down, until golden, 4 to 5 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to a plate and pour off half the fat from skillet."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Return skillet to medium heat and add garlic, thyme, and red pepper flakes. Cook until fragrant, 1 minute, then stir in broth, heavy cream, sun-dried tomatoes, and Parmesan and season with more salt. Bring to a simmer, then return chicken to skillet, skin-side up."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Transfer skillet to oven and bake until chicken is cooked through (and juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a knife), 17 to 20 minutes."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Garnish with basil and serve."
